Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. Commitment for Failure to Furnish Bail.

BAIL HEARING - 
Defendant in custody and appearing by video from the Manitowoc County Jail.  The State informs the Court that the defendant will be charged with the crime of possess cocaine, possess fentanyl with intent to deliver, possess drug paraphernalia and felony bail jumping.  The matter is continued for initial appearance on 07-18-22 at 1:30 p.m.  Bail is set at $250.00 cash bond with the conditions that defendant must maintain absolute sobriety from alcohol and drugs except for prescribed medications taken in prescribed doses and defendant is not to possess any controlled substances or drug paraphernalia. Bail not furnished and defendant is remanded to the custody of the Sheriff.
